Lyn Goleby, the Managing Director of Picturehouse Cinemas at the Hackney Picturehouse, London October 25th, 2011. Ben Gurr
Nic Fildes
Published at 12:01AM, December 7 2012
Two miles separate the garish multiplex cinema in Wandsworth from the bijou picture house in neighbouring Clapham. However, the two cinemas have split the community with well-heeled art-house movie fans opting for the Clapham Picturehouse and popcorn-munching teenagers happier in the brightly lit Cineworld up the road.
Cineworld, Britain’s largest cinema chain, is to bridge that cultural gap after agreeing to buy the Picturehouse chain for £47.3 million. It argued that the deal would add a more “discerning” audience than those that visit its 80 suburban multiplexes.
